fallback.description: A fallback function that is triggered when the contract receives ether without data.

constructor.description: Initializes the contract with the specified implementation contract address.

changeAdmin.description: Changes the admin of the contract to a new address.

implementation.description: Returns the address of the implementation contract.

upgradeTo.description: Upgrades the contract to a new implementation address.

upgradeToAndCall.description: Upgrades the contract to a new implementation address and calls a function on the new implementation.

AdminChanged.description: Emitted when the admin of the contract is changed.

Upgraded.description: Emitted when the contract is upgraded to a new implementation.
